      • phoneVerification

        public PhoneVerification phoneVerification(java.lang.String phoneNumber,
                                           java.lang.String includeNetworkInfo)
                                    throws ApiException
        Phone verification. This service accepts a phone number as input and returns details distinguishing landline and wireless numbers and also checks if a wireless number can be located.
        Parameters:
        phoneNumber - E.164 formatted phone number. Accepts digits only. Country Code (1) optional for USA & CAN. (required)
        includeNetworkInfo - Y or N (default is Y) – if it is N, then network/carrier details will not be added in the response. (optional)
        Returns:
        PhoneVerification
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
